---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Jun Nammoku | Tech Blog
lang: en
---
{% set posts = collections.enPosts %}
<header class="site-header">
  <div class="container nav-shell">
    <a class="brand-mark" href="/index.html">Jun Nammoku</a>
    <nav class="nav-group" aria-label="Primary">
      <button class="nav-toggle" type="button" data-nav-toggle aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="blog-navigation">
        <span class="nav-toggle-label">Menu</span>
        <i class="fa-solid fa-bars" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </button>
      <div class="nav-links" id="blog-navigation" data-nav-menu>
        <a href="/index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="/en/portfolio/">Portfolio</a>
        <a href="/en/blog/" aria-current="page">Blog</a>
        <a href="/index.html#contact">Contact</a>
        <div class="nav-language" aria-label="Language">
          <span class="nav-language-label">Language</span>
          <div class="nav-language-options">
            <a class="nav-language-link is-active" href="/en/blog/" aria-current="page">EN</a>
            <a class="nav-language-link" href="/ja/blog/">JA</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<main>
  <section class="hero blog-hero" id="blog-hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid blog-hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tech Blog</p>
        <h1 class="hero-title">Engineering notes &amp; playbooks</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">
          Deep dives on building resilient platforms, automation blueprints, and lessons learned from real-world incidents. Expect concise walkthroughs with architecture diagrams, guardrails, and code-ready snippets.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="cta-button primary" href="#posts">Browse latest posts</a>
          <a class="cta-button ghost" href="#newsletter">Request a topic</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-pane" aria-label="Blog focus areas">
        <h2>Publishing themes</h2>
        <ul class="hero-list">
          <li>Operations stories from regulated AWS environments</li>
          <li>Infrastructure as Code patterns across CDK, Terraform, and Pulumi</li>
          <li>Observability guardrails, cost controls, and platform governance</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="hero-metrics">
          <div class="metric-chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-diagram-project" aria-hidden="true"></i> Architecture retros</div>
          <div class="metric-chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Automation workflows</div>
          <div class="metric-chip"><i class="fa-solid fa-shield" aria-hidden="true"></i> Security guardrails</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section blog-controls" id="filters">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="blog-control-panel">
        <form class="blog-search" role="search">
          <label class="sr-only" for="blog-search-input">Search articles</label>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-search" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          <input id="blog-search-input" type="search" name="search" placeholder="Search architectures, IaC, incident reviews..." autocomplete="off">
          <button type="submit">Search</button>
        </form>
        <div class="tag-stack" aria-label="Trending tags">
          <span class="tag-stack-label">Trending tags</span>
          <ul class="tag-list" role="list">
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill is-active" aria-pressed="true">AWS</button></li>
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill" aria-pressed="false">IaC</button></li>
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill" aria-pressed="false">Security</button></li>
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill" aria-pressed="false">Operations</button></li>
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill" aria-pressed="false">Serverless</button></li>
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill" aria-pressed="false">Observability</button></li>
            <li><button type="button" class="tag-pill" aria-pressed="false">Culture</button></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section blog-feed" id="posts">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="blog-layout">
        <div class="post-feed">
          {% if posts | length %}
            {% for post in posts %}
              <article class="post-card{% if loop.first %} featured{% endif %}">
                <a class="post-link" href="{{ post.url | url }}">
                  <div class="post-meta">
                    <span>{{ post.data.category | default('General') }}</span>
                    <span>{{ post.date | date('MMM d, yyyy') }}{% if post.data.duration %} · {{ post.data.duration }}{% endif %}</span>
                  </div>
                  <h2 class="post-title">{{ post.data.title }}</h2>
                  <p class="post-description">{{ post.data.description | default('Stay tuned for detailed notes on platform engineering, automation, and incidents.') }}</p>
                  {% if post.data.tags %}
                    <div class="post-tags">
                      {% for tag in post.data.tags %}
                        <span class="tag-pill">{{ tag }}</span>
                      {% endfor %}
                    </div>
                  {% endif %}
                  <footer>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    <span>{{ post.data.cta | default('Read article') }}</span>
                  </footer>
                </a>
              </article>
            {% endfor %}
          {% else %}
            <article class="post-card placeholder">
              <div class="post-link" aria-label="No posts yet">
                <div class="post-meta">
                  <span>Status</span>
                  <span>Publishing soon</span>
                </div>
                <h2 class="post-title">No articles published yet</h2>
                <p class="post-description">
                  The first batch of articles is in production—check back soon for fresh engineering deep dives.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>
          {% endif %}
        </div>

        <aside class="blog-sidebar" aria-label="Blog sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Trending on the blog</h3>
            {% if posts | length %}
              <ol class="trend-list">
                {% for trend in posts | head(3) %}
                  <li>
                    <a href="{{ trend.url | url }}">{{ trend.data.title }}</a>
                    <span>{{ trend.data.category | default('General') }}{% if trend.data.duration %} · {{ trend.data.duration }}{% endif %}</span>
                  </li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ol>
            {% else %}
              <p>Trending posts will appear here once the first stories go live. Stay tuned.</p>
            {% endif %}
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Series &amp; collections</h3>
            {% if collections.series_en %}
              <ul class="series-list">
                {% for series in collections.series_en %}
                  <li>{{ series }}</li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ul>
            {% else %}
              <p>Series and curated collections launch soon. Watch this space for guided reading paths.</p>
            {% endif %}
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section blog-footer-cta" id="newsletter">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="blog-footer-card">
        <h2>Have a challenge worth dissecting?</h2>
        <p>
          Share the context behind your next migration, incident, or platform initiative. I love turning real-world constraints into shareable patterns others can reuse.
        </p>
        <div class="footer-cta-actions">
          <a class="cta-button primary" href="mailto:jun.nammoku@gmail.com">Pitch a story</a>
          <a class="cta-button ghost" href="/index.html#contact">Book a consult</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<button id="scrollTopBtn" type="button" aria-label="Scroll to top">
  <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-up" aria-hidden="true"></i>
</button>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="container">
    <p>&copy; 2025 Jun Nammoku. Built with curiosity and automation.</p>
  </div>
</footer>
